---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="What to bring us | Healey Cottage">
  <header class="head">
    <p class="eyebrow">Entirely optional</p>
    <h1>If you’re asking what to bring us</h1>
    <p class="lead intro">
      Since this question comes up a lot: your presence is the main event. But if you feel like arriving with a small peace offering, here are the kinds of things that reliably go over well.
    </p>
    <p class="fine">
      This is not a registry, a demand, or the beginning of a dowry system. It is simply a lightly curated guide to host-friendly gestures.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="grid" aria-label="Suggested host gifts">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Consumables We Always Like</h2>
      <p class="muted">Easy wins. No guesswork. Rarely controversial.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Whole coffee beans</li>
        <li>Snacks and sharing foods</li>
        <li>Wine you would be happy to drink yourself</li>
        <li>Sweet treats</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Cottage Usefuls</h2>
      <p class="muted">Practical things that somehow never stop being useful up north.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Bug spray</li>
        <li>Sunscreen</li>
        <li>Firewood bundle</li>
        <li>A thoughtful grocery add-on for the weekend</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Delightfully Extra</h2>
      <p class="muted">Not necessary, but always appreciated when chosen with taste and restraint.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>A dramatic host gift</li>
        <li>Champagne</li>
        <li>A small bouquet of flowers</li>
        <li>Any contribution that feels charming rather than burdensome</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card caution">
      <h2>Please Don’t Bring</h2>
      <p class="muted">This section exists to protect everyone’s future selves.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Random decorative objects we now have to own forever</li>
        <li>Novelty junk that becomes our responsibility after checkout</li>
        <li>Mystery perishables with an unclear plan</li>
        <li>Anything large, inconvenient, or spiritually from Winners</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="closing card">
    <h2>The Rule of Thumb</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      If it is easy to enjoy, easy to share, and easy to finish by the end of the weekend, you are almost certainly in the right zone.
    </p>
    <p class="fine">
      And again: this is entirely optional. Showing up pleasant, relaxed, and ready for lake time remains the gold standard.
    </p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .head {
      margin-top: 10px;
      display: grid;
      gap: 10px;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: rgba(131, 75, 25, 0.82);
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0;
    }

    .intro {
      margin: 0;
      max-width: 62ch;
    }

    .fine {
      margin: 0;
      max-width: 70ch;
    }

    .grid {
      margin-top: 22px;
      display: grid;
      gap: 14px;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    @media (max-width: 760px) {
      .grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }

    .card {
      border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 16px 18px;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.96), rgba(247, 244, 238, 0.92));
      box-shadow: 0 10px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
    }

    .card h2 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
    }

    .card p {
      margin: 8px 0 0;
    }

    .card ul {
      margin: 12px 0 0;
      padding-left: 18px;
      display: grid;
      gap: 8px;
    }

    .caution {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 250, 247, 0.98), rgba(248, 240, 235, 0.94));
    }

    .closing {
      margin-top: 18px;
    }

    .closing .lead {
      margin: 8px 0 0;
      max-width: 58ch;
    }

    .closing .fine {
      margin-top: 10px;
    }

    @media (min-width: 861px) {
      .intro,
      .fine,
      .closing .lead {
        max-width: none;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Base>
